    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "1f5ba59f_66ab9b0d",
        "filename": "handler/handler_main.cc",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 513,
      "author": {
        "id": 1212939
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-07-30T22:59:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think it\u0027s better if we can switch between users\u0027 home dir and here as users log in and out. It\u0027s just more work since this is out of process from Chrome and a new message between Chrome and this crashpad_handler needs to be build for that. And it\u0027s not really necessary since the log messages are very limited and they don\u0027t contain PII now.",
      "parentUuid": "6d88cb20_9110b364",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 513,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 513,
        "endChar": 66
      },
      "revId": "0d03675609fb34c78a52a1fd3233f70d4fe4c40e",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "8dafa0a5_07ca2ff7",
        "filename": "handler/linux/crash_report_exception_handler.cc",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 66,
      "author": {
        "id": 1172779
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-07-18T00:52:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t think we need to duplicate this logic here in Crashpad. Passing this flag around to the right process types is already handled by Chrome.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 57,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 66,
        "endChar": 1
      },
      "revId": "0d03675609fb34c78a52a1fd3233f70d4fe4c40e",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "7c769a36_57d5746e",
        "filename": "handler/linux/crash_report_exception_handler.cc",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 66,
      "author": {
        "id": 1212939
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-07-30T22:59:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "crashpad_handler needs to know if it needs to pass the timestamp to crash_reporter and crashpad_handler knows the process_type when it\u0027s called by the different Chrome processes when they crash. How else is crashpad_handler knows?",
      "parentUuid": "8dafa0a5_07ca2ff7",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 57,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 66,
        "endChar": 1
      },
      "revId": "0d03675609fb34c78a52a1fd3233f70d4fe4c40e",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e5f541e5_44511cfc",
        "filename": "handler/linux/crash_report_exception_handler.cc",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 66,
      "author": {
        "id": 1172779
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-08-05T18:38:19Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Only passing the flag when crash_loop_before_time !\u003d 0 should be sufficient.",
      "parentUuid": "7c769a36_57d5746e",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 57,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 66,
        "endChar": 1
