    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "23f3d0cb_1736795a",
        "filename": "handler/linux/crash_report_exception_handler.cc",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 247,
      "author": {
        "id": 1172779
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-07-18T00:52:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Do we need to continue writing the dumps like this? Why can\u0027t crash_reporter extract these keys from a plain old minidump itself?\n\nIf we do need to re-write the minidump like this, we can use an HTTPMultipartBuilder to do this. We did this on Android to avoid modifying its minidump uploader: https://osscs.corp.google.com/chromium/chromium/src/+/master:components/minidump_uploader/rewrite_minidumps_as_mimes.cc;l\u003d129",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 236,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 247,
        "endChar": 5
      },
      "revId": "0d03675609fb34c78a52a1fd3233f70d4fe4c40e",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "abecbf50_c584389b",
        "filename": "handler/linux/crash_report_exception_handler.cc",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 247,
      "author": {
        "id": 1212939
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-07-30T22:59:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "crash_reporter code is in Chrome OS repository, which is separate from the Chrome one. At this time Chrome OS doesn\u0027t use crashpad and has not imported crashpad library. So crash_reporter has no access to crashpad code and specifically no access to the code to extract these values from the minidumps.\ncrash_reporter already handles this Chrome OS specific TLV format data file. That\u0027s why I\u0027m writing the data with this format instead of modifying crash_reporter to use another format.",
      "parentUuid": "23f3d0cb_1736795a",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 236,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 247,
        "endChar": 5
      },
      "revId": "0d03675609fb34c78a52a1fd3233f70d4fe4c40e",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
