    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "de5fcec0_e6566ec9",
        "filename": "handler/linux/crash_report_exception_handler.cc",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 304,
      "author": {
        "id": 1172779
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-07-18T00:52:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m not familiar with subtleties of memfd_create(). Do we need any synchronization with crash_reporter here (i.e. a waitpid())? What happens if crashpad_handler exits before crash_reporter is finished with the file? Does the memory backing the file get preserved somewhere if this process has exited and crash_reporter has called execv()?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 297,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 304,
        "endChar": 24
      },
      "revId": "0d03675609fb34c78a52a1fd3233f70d4fe4c40e",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "06ad100b_ffd26731",
        "filename": "handler/linux/crash_report_exception_handler.cc",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 304,
      "author": {
        "id": 1212939
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-07-30T22:59:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is what the memfd_create manual says:\n       With respect to fork(2) and execve(2), the usual semantics apply for\n       the file descriptor created by memfd_create().  A copy of the file\n       descriptor is inherited by the child produced by fork(2) and refers\n       to the same file.  The file descriptor is preserved across execve(2),\n       unless the close-on-exec flag has been set.",
      "parentUuid": "de5fcec0_e6566ec9",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 297,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 304,
        "endChar": 24
      },
      "revId": "0d03675609fb34c78a52a1fd3233f70d4fe4c40e",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "550d350a_824bee80",
        "filename": "handler/linux/crash_report_exception_handler.h",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 88,
      "author": {
        "id": 1172779
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-07-18T00:52:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t think we need to define this out. As long as we don\u0027t pass a --url option to the handler, this upload thread won\u0027t be created.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 88,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 88,
        "endChar": 25
      },
      "revId": "0d03675609fb34c78a52a1fd3233f70d4fe4c40e",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
